I see the problem. The toolbar CSS variables are defined on `.editor-container`:

```css
.editor-container {
    --editor-bg: var(--bg-elevated);
    --editor-text: var(--text-primary);
    --editor-border: var(--border-light);
    --editor-accent: var(--accent-purple);
}
```

But in ChapterEditor, there's no `.editor-container` element. The outer wrapper is `.chapter-editor-page`. So when the toolbar uses `var(--editor-bg)`, `var(--editor-text)`, etc., they're undefined and fall back to... nothing (initial value, which for `background-color` is `transparent` and for `fill` is... depends).


When CSS custom properties are undefined, they resolve to their initial values—so `background-color` becomes transparent and SVG `fill` defaults to black, which explains why the toolbar icons disappear in dark mode. I need to define these variables on `.chapter-editor-page` instead.

