### Part 4: ChapterCommentCard -- Individual Comment Display

**New file: `C:\Users\johnm\iskrib_v3\client\src\components\Stories\ChapterReader\ChapterCommentCard.jsx`**

This is a simplified version of the existing `CommentsCards` at `C:\Users\johnm\iskrib_v3\client\src\components\comments\commentsCards.jsx`, adapted for the story comment data shape (which returns nested `replies` directly instead of requiring a separate fetch).

Key differences from the existing `CommentsCards`:
- No infinite query for replies -- replies are already nested in the API response
- Only 2-level threading (top-level comments + replies; replies cannot have sub-replies)
- Uses the `users` join data shape from story_comments (`users.username` is available)
- 300 char limit instead of 200

```jsx
const ChapterCommentCard = ({ comment, onReply, isReply = false }) => {
    const { user } = useAuth();
    const navigate = useNavigate();
    const clickProfile = handleClickProfile(navigate);
    const [showReplies, setShowReplies] = useState(false);

    return (
        <div className={`ccc-card ${isReply ? 'ccc-card-reply' : ''}`}>
            {isReply && <div className="ccc-thread-line" />}

            <div className="ccc-content">
                <div className="ccc-user-row">
                    <div
                        className={`ccc-avatar-ring ${comment.users?.badge === 'legend' ? 'ccc-ring-legend' : comment.users?.badge === 'og' ? 'ccc-ring-og' : ''}`}
                        onClick={(e) => clickProfile(e, user?.userData?.[0]?.id, comment.users?.id, comment.users?.username)}
                    >
                        <img className="ccc-avatar" src={comment.users?.image_url || '/assets/profile.jpg'} alt="" />
                    </div>
                    <span className="ccc-name" onClick={(e) => clickProfile(e, user?.userData?.[0]?.id, comment.users?.id, comment.users?.username)}>
                        {comment.users?.name}
                    </span>
                    <VerifiedBadge badge={comment.users?.badge} size={13} />
                    <span className="ccc-dot">&middot;</span>
                    <span className="ccc-date">{formatPostDate(comment.created_at)}</span>
                </div>

                <p className="ccc-body">{comment.comment}</p>

                <div className="ccc-actions">
                    {!isReply && (
                        <button className="ccc-reply-btn" onClick={() => onReply(comment.id, comment.users?.name)}>
                            Reply
                        </button>
                    )}
                    {!isReply && comment.replies?.length > 0 && (
                        <button className="ccc-toggle-replies" onClick={() => setShowReplies(!showReplies)}>
                            {showReplies ? 'Hide' : 'Show'} {comment.replies.length} {comment.replies.length === 1 ? 'reply' : 'replies'}
                        </button>
                    )}
                </div>

                <AnimatePresence>
                    {showReplies && comment.replies?.map(reply => (
                        <motion.div
                            key={reply.id}
                            initial={{ opacity: 0 }}
                            animate={{ opacity: 1 }}
                            exit={{ opacity: 0 }}
                        >
                            <ChapterCommentCard comment={reply} onReply={onReply} isReply={true} />
                        </motion.div>
                    ))}
                </AnimatePresence>
            </div>
        </div>
    );
};
```

