### Part 7: Mobile Responsive Considerations

The `window.innerWidth` or a simple media query hook determines mobile vs. desktop behavior:

```jsx
// Simple hook or inline check
const useIsMobile = (breakpoint = 768) => {
    const [isMobile, setIsMobile] = useState(window.innerWidth <= breakpoint);
    useEffect(() => {
        const handler = () => setIsMobile(window.innerWidth <= breakpoint);
        window.addEventListener('resize', handler);
        return () => window.removeEventListener('resize', handler);
    }, [breakpoint]);
    return isMobile;
};
```

This can be defined inline in `CommentPanel.jsx` or extracted to a utility. Since the codebase does not appear to have a shared media query hook, define it locally in the CommentPanel file.

On mobile:
- Badge layer uses reduced sizing (handled by CSS media queries)
- CommentPanel renders as a bottom sheet (70vh) instead of a right panel
- The paragraph preview area is more compact
- Tapping a badge opens the panel; there is no hover state (touch devices)

